The segmentation by platform, including internal brokerage enablement and external brokerage enablement, caters to organizations looking to streamline cloud service delivery within their operations or extend services to external clients. The deployment mode segmentation into public, private, and hybrid clouds further enhances the market's adaptability to varying security and control needs. Public cloud deployment offers cost-effective services over the internet, managed by third-party providers, while private cloud deployment ensures dedicated resources for enhanced security and control. Hybrid cloud deployment combines the benefits of both public and private clouds, allowing businesses to leverage the strengths of each model based on their specific requirements.

